      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "### Problem Statement:\n",
        "We would like to apply the Sobel Edge filter manually on an image.\n",
        "\n",
        "The Sobel operator, sometimes called the Sobelâ€“Feldman operator or Sobel filter, is used in image processing and computer vision, particularly within edge detection algorithms where it creates an image emphasising edges.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "#### Steps:\n",
        "1. Research the 2-D matrix of Sobel Edge Filter\n",
        "2. Load an image to a 3 dimensional array (Red, Green, Blue channels) (hint: You can use `PIL` library for this\n",
        "3. Pick-up one of the 3 channels and turn that 3D object into a 2D array\n",
        "3. Build a function to apply Sobel Filter as we traverse across the 2D dimension\n",
        "4. Display the resulted image using `matplotlib`"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "W-r5i-zwKZ8Q"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Step 1: Research the 2-D matrix of Sobel Edge Filter\n",
        "\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "BSy0m2vnLfrR"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "\n",
        "filter = np.array(\n",
        "    [\n",
        "        [1,2,1],[0,0,0],[-1,-2,-1]\n",
        "    ]\n",
        ")"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "FmysAV5JLgjQ"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Step 2: Load an image to a 3 dimensional array (Red, Green, Blue channels) (hint: You can use PIL library for this"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "l7UrU_ILLft9"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "from PIL import Image\n",
        "from numpy import asarray\n",
        "\n",
        "image = Image.open('/content/022421_mt_number-generator_feat.jpg')\n",
        "\n",
        "data = asarray(image)\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "from matplotlib import pyplot as plt\n",
        "plt.imshow(data[:,:,0], interpolation=\"nearest\", cmap=\"Greys\")\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Aay0owkULhEd",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 240
        },
        "outputId": "d3d7b0f8-d2cd-4112-e7b0-e927dbdea1e7"

      "execution_count": null,

              "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"

            "image/png": "\n"
          },
          "metadata": {

          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Step 3: Pick-up one of the 3 channels and turn that 3D object into a 2D array"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "d86IVhOVLfw3"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "data2D = data[:,:,2]"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "YcldGB7DLhqP"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Step 4: Build a function to apply Sobel Filter as we traverse across the 2D dimension"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "XRPY3ocfLf3Y"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "newData = np.tile(0,(data2D.shape[0],data2D.shape[1]))\n",
        "print(data2D)\n",
        "\n",
        "for x in range(0,data2D.shape[0]-3,1):\n",
        "  for y in range(0,data2D.shape[1]-3,1):\n",
        "    newData[x,y] = np.sum(data2D[x:x+3,y:y+3] * filter)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(newData)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
